i'm in google sheets and i'm trying to enter the text "+3 foo" without quotes and it keeps giving error
ChatGPT said:

In Google Sheets, when you start a cell entry with +, Sheets interprets it as a formula, which is why you're getting an error.

To enter text like +3 foo without it being treated as a formula, you can add a single quote (') at the beginning of the text. The single quote tells Google Sheets that the following is plain text, not a formula.

So, try entering it as:

vbnet
'+3 foo

The single quote won't be visible in the cell but will ensure the content is treated as text.

You said:
what is the term for when you reskin or retheme a card game or board game and keep the game mechanics identical but just give it different theme? what is most common term for that?
ChatGPT said:

The most common term for when you reskin or retheme a card game or board game while keeping the game mechanics identical is "retheme". This is the term typically used in the board game community to describe the process of changing the thematic elements (story, setting, characters, art) of a game while leaving the core mechanics unchanged.

Sometimes, people also use "reskin", which comes from video game terminology, but "retheme" is more specific to board games.
